text.tspan: Investors front capital then receive dividends/shares

tspan.tspan: : By far the most common. Easier to
raise capital, but no control by customers. Can be
abusive and usually requires a deal of regulation to
ensure a reasonable amount of net social benefit.

text.tspan: Cooperative: Harder to raise capital, but more
customer control and potentially less expensive.
SC Cooperative: One of the most difficult and
expensive aspects of a coop are automated away.
